title.narrative: Abidjan-Lagos Trade and Transport Facilitation Project (ALTTFP)

description.narrative: The objective of the ALTTFP (APL1) is to reduce trade and transport barriers in the ports and on the roads along the Abidjan-Lagos corridor in Ghana, Togo, and Benin.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.A.2 | Description :GH, TG and BN shall maintain their respective Project CoordinationUnits (PCU) throughout Project implementation with functions and responsibilities acceptable to IDA and with staff in adequatenumber | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.A.5 | Description: GH, TG & BN shall each: (i)Furnish IDA for reviewannual work plans,budget, counterpart funds & other financing, for activities for following year & (ii) allocate suchfunds & plan as IDA approved |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II.B.4 | Description :GH, TG and BN shall each appoint an external auditor on the basis ofTOR and with qualifications and experience satisfactory to IDA not later than 4 months after the Effectiveness Date. | Due Date:01-Dec-2010

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I.E.2 | Description: GH and TG shall pay the amounts specified in their respective (RAPs)that are required to be paid as compensation to the Displaced Persons. | Due Date :31-May-2013
